bers of the Board of Trustee, the Undergraduate Student Government and Undergraduate Members of the UIC Senate. EPC believes in and supports the philosophy that open, fair, and well-organized elections play an essential part in strengthening our community and student governance at UIC. Each year, EPC is responsible for ensuring a fair election by adjudicating all campaign-related matters, including alleged campaign violations and clarifications to the Rules and Regulations, and ratifying the election results.      EPC Handbook  Student Election Rules & Regulations       EPC will conduct the following elections:     Undergraduate Student Government         Undergraduate Student Government:   President (1 total)  Vice-President (1 total)  House of Representatives (30 total)        Illinois Board of Trustees         Illinois Board of Trustees   Student Member of the Board of Trustees (1 total)        UIC Senate         Undergraduate Student Senator (20 total)   Undergraduate Student Senator (20 total)            Official Complaints - 2020        Complainant: Jocelyn Aranda-Ortiz  Respondent(s): Wasan Kumar & Jocelyn Bravo          Complainant: Wasan Kumar  Respondent(s): Jocelyn Aranda-Ortiz & Marian Udoetuk          Complainant: David Shipyor  Respondent(s): Jocelyn Bravo, Wasan Kumar, & Hana Ahmed          Complainant: Jocelyn Bravo  Respondent(s): David Shipyor          Complainant: David Shipyor  Respondent(s): John Donners          Content        Submit A Complaint  Official Complaint Process          Contact EPC  Have Questions/Concerns?           Interested in joining? Thank you for your interest. We are not currently accepting applications at this time.      Keep an eye out for updates!       Interested in joining?        Check icon        Apply Here!        Envelope icon         Questions?             About    Back to main content           Our Work, Mission and Values    Our Team    Student Handbook     UIC History, Traditions, Symbols    Student Life    Stud